S. E. C. CORPORATION, formerly known as Canaday Cooler Co., Inc., Plaintiff-Appellant, v. UNITED STATES of America, Defendant-Appellee. No. 228, Docket 24175. United States Court of Appeals Second Circuit. Argued Feb. 8, 1957. Decided Feb. 25, 1957. Rollin Browne, of Satterlee, Browne & Cherbonnier, New York City (Irving Levine, New York City, on the brief), for plaintiff-appellant. Miriam R. Goldman, Asst. U. S. Atty., New York City (Paul W. Williams, U. S. Atty., New York City, on the brief), for defendant-appellee.

Before CLARK, Chief Judge, MEDINA, Circuit Judge, and J. JOSEPH SMITH, District Judge.

PER CURIAM.

Affirmed on the opinion of District Judge Palmieri, D.C.S.D.N.Y., 140 F. Supp. 717.
